Date: Wed, 9 Jul 2026 14:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Skip sync chunk load in setInitialSpawn for Folia

On Folia/Canvas, CraftServer.createWorld runs on the global region tick
thread. setInitialSpawn calls PlayerSpawnFinder.getLevelRespawnPos which
synchronously loads chunks via ChunkTaskScheduler.syncLoadNonFull. This
blocks the global tick for 5-10 seconds, triggering FoliaWatchdogThread
timeouts.

Fix: skip the synchronous spawn point search when running in region
threading mode. Use (0, 64, 0) as fallback spawn and let the first
player join trigger async chunk loading. The spawn area is still
prepared normally by the prepareSpawnArea code that follows.

diff --git a/net/minecraft/server/MinecraftServer.java b/net/minecraft/server/MinecraftServer.java
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/net/minecraft/server/MinecraftServer.java
+++ b/net/minecraft/server/MinecraftServer.java
@@ -860,6 +860,13 @@ public abstract class MinecraftServer {
     }
 
     private void setInitialSpawn(ServerLevel world, WorldData worldData, boolean generateBonusChest, boolean debugWorld) {
+        // Canvas start - skip sync chunk load in setInitialSpawn for region threading
+        // PlayerSpawnFinder.getLevelRespawnPos calls ChunkTaskScheduler.syncLoadNonFull which blocks
+        // the global region tick thread for 5-10 seconds, triggering watchdog timeouts.
+        if (io.papermc.paper.threadedregions.RegionizedServer.isGlobalTickThread()) {
+            return; // Skip spawn point search; world default spawn (0,64,0) is used instead
+        }
+        // Canvas end
         boolean flag = world.serverLevelData().getGameType() == GameType.SPECTATOR;
         boolean flag1 = this.serverLevelData.getGameRules().getBoolean(GameRules.RULE_DO_WARDEN_SPAWNING);
         if (!flag && !flag1) {
